ElementDescription: Respondent
Teen subject ID the parent is reporting on

Sometimes things happen to people that are unusually or especially frightening, horrible, or traumatic(ex. a serious accident or fire, a physical or sexual assault or abuse, an earthquake or flood, a war, seeing someone be killed or seriously injured, having a loved one die through homicide or suicide). Have you ever experienced this kind of event?
In the past month, have you had nightmares about the event(s) or thought about the event(s) when you did not want to?
In the past month, have you tried hard not to think about the event(s) or went out of your way to avoid situations that reminded you of the event(s)?
In the past month, have you been constantly on guard, watchful, or easily startled?
In the past month, have you felt numb or detached from people, activities, or your surroundings?
In the past month, have you felt guilty or unable to stop blaming yourself or others for the event(s) or any problems the event(s) may have caused?
When answering these items, which type of events were you considering? (Mark all that apply) Life-threatening illness or injury
When answering these items, which type of events were you considering? (Mark all that apply) Exposure to community violence (for example, gun shots, gang violence, homicides)
When answering these items, which type of events were you considering? (Mark all that apply) Natural Disaster (for example a flood, hurricane, tornado, earthquake, fire)
When answering these items, which type of events were you considering? (Mark all that apply) Transportation accident (for example a car accident, train wreck, plane crash)
When answering these items, which type of events were you considering? (Mark all that apply) Physical assault (for example being attacked, threatened with a weapon, beaten up)
When answering these items, which type of events were you considering? (Mark all that apply) Sexual assault (for example rape, attempted rape, unwanted sexual contact)
When answering these items, which type of events were you considering? (Mark all that apply) Emotional or verbal abuse (for example, people in my family repeatedly insulted me)
When answering these items, which type of events were you considering? (Mark all that apply) Combat or exposure to a war zone (either in the military or as a civilian)
When answering these items, which type of events were you considering? (Mark all that apply) Sudden violent or accidental death of someone you know (for example, suicide or homicide)
